# EXAMPLE armv7 SOURCE-BUILD PARTITION lock (NON-ACTIVE schema fixture; NOT read by install/update).
#
# ROLE: this is the DERIVED six-entry build lock -- exactly the approved source-built packages
# (cffi, httptools, markupsafe, psutil, pyyaml, uvloop). It is NOT a complete solution of
# requirements.txt: the other 24 packages are the REUSE partition, authorized by
# release/builder/armv7-reuse-authz.json instead. Validate it with
# ccc_release.validate_build_partition_lock(), NEVER with the complete-solution validator
# (release/lock_validate.py) -- that would reject it for "missing" reuse-partition packages.
#
# PROVENANCE: the real file is a DERIVED output of release/builder/gen_active_inputs.py (never
# hand-written, never produced by gen_locks.py) and is committed ATOMICALLY together with the
# 24-entry reuse authorization. Until that generator has been run BOTH derived files are absent
# (the legal `pre_generation` state); exactly one present is an invalid half-state.
#
# CONTENT: PyPI SDIST sha256 -- the build-input authorization used to fetch sources before building
# the armv7 wheels; the post-build provenance record then binds each sdist -> wheel. Versions mirror
# the durable 30-pin requirements-armv7-solution.lock (the generator input).

